ter level and climatic data sets are available the PIRFICT method provides an independent assessment of recharge. Importantly, the PIRFICT method highlights the need to consider the lag between rainfall and recharge at the water table. This lag is often overlooked when calibrating spatial distributed water balance models used to guide groundwater allocations.},
